## The Prompt Cookbook

Pick a prompt based on what you want. From most open-ended to most specific.

### "Take the wheel" — Full Autonomy

> Go. Find what needs improving and improve it.

> Run an improvement cycle. Use your judgment on what to tackle.

> I have an hour. Make the {{project}} better. Check in with me at the end.

> What's the single highest-impact thing we could improve right now? Investigate and fix it.

### "Explore and advise" — Discovery Mode

> Look at the {{project}} with fresh eyes. What are we doing wrong? What are we missing?

> Have the scrutinizer challenge our entire approach. Is the architecture right?

> Read the codebase and tell me honestly: what would you refactor first?

> If you were rebuilding this from scratch, what would you do differently?

### "Focus on {{AREA}}" — Targeted

<!-- Bootstrap: Add 3-5 project-specific prompts per focus area. Examples: -->

> The UI is inconsistent across pages. Fix the spacing, colours, and component usage.

> The API error handling is weak. Audit all endpoints and add proper error responses.

> Performance is slow on {{page}}. Profile it and fix the bottlenecks.

> Run the test suite and fix any failures. Then add tests for {{untested area}}.

### "Fix a specific issue" — Surgical

> Fix {{specific bug description}}. The issue is in {{file/area}}.

> Refactor {{component}} to use {{pattern}}. Don't change behavior, just structure.

### "Review and status" — Check Progress

> What have we changed so far? Show me the improvement trend.

> Read the last 3 cycle summaries and give me an honest assessment: are we making progress?

> What's in the backlog? Reprioritise based on what we've learned.

> Have the reviewer do a thorough quality check on the current state.

