## Git — Checkpoints & Reverting

The agents commit checkpoints automatically before and after changes. You can also use git directly:

```bash
# See what changed since last commit
git diff

# See recent history
git log --oneline -10

# Revert everything back to last commit
git checkout -- .

# Revert a specific file
git checkout -- path/to/file

# See all tags (milestones)
git tag -l
```

If something goes very wrong:

> Revert all changes back to [commit hash or tag]. Start fresh from there.

